
################
#### README ####
################

#BUILD
download project, cd project directory and run the comment "ant jar"

#INTRO
First you need a mail and an user key.
Login in GDV and go to 'preferences' page you will have your personal user key.
Now there is two way : you can use the jar file provided or send by yourself
a POST connection to "http://svitsrv25.epfl.ch/gdv/post". Note that if you send a POST
by yourself you will have to add the parameter "id=gdv_post" in your request.

#DEFINITION OF THE PARAMETERS

REQUESTED :
	- mail : login in tequila
	- key  : user key
	- command : one of [new_project, add_track,add_sqlite]

REQUESTED BY COMMAND :
->'new_project' :
	- seq_id : the nr_assembly id of the species in Genrep
	- name : name of the project
	- public (OPTIONNAL default=false): true to make the project public
	RESPONSE : a JSON String : {"project_id":<anID>,"public_url":<anURL>}

->'add_track' :
	- url : url to fetch
	- project_id : the project id in GDV
	- name (OPTIONNAL default=name of the file): the name you want to give to the track

->'add_sqlite' :
	- url : url to fetch
	- project_id : the project id in GDV
	- datatype : one of [qualitative,quantitative] N.B :QUALITATIVE does not work yet
	- name (OPTIONNAL default=name of the file): the name you want to give to the track

#REQUESTS EXAMPLES
1) Want to create a public project in your profile for yeast?
	$java -jar --mail <your mail> -key <your user key> --command new_project --seq_id 98 --name TestProject --public true
		- or -
	POST at http://svitsrv25.epfl.ch/gdv_dev/post
	with body = "id=gdv_post&mail=<your mail>&key=<your user key>&command=new_projectseq_id=98&name=TestProject&public=true 
	It will give you back an ID and an URL if you made it public. This is the project id in GDV and	the URL	you can	give to	
	someone	else (e.g. {"project_id":5622,"public_url":"http://svitsrv25.epfl.ch/gdv/browser?id=5622&ukey=ol9iio7k11&pkey=sg67v1ceqo83"}

2) Want to add a track to a project ?
	$java -jar  --mail <your mail> -key <your user key> --command add_track --url <http://salt/BED/myfile.wig> --project_id <project id>
	for POST, see (1).  (don't forget to add id=gdv_post to the request's body)

3) Want to add a track in sqlite format ?
	$java -jar  --mail <your mail> -key <your user key> --command add_sqlite --url <http://salt/BED/myfile.db> --project_id <project id> --datatype quantitative
	(qualitative not working for the moment)